{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AViKkDDw3pjyiEgEBes9R5","type":"tool_result","content":"   251→function openDrawer(workflowName, stepName) {\n   252→    var wf = workflowsData.find(function(w) { return w.name === workflowName; });\n   253→    if (!wf) return;\n   254→    var step = wf.steps.find(function(s) { return s.name === stepName; });\n   255→    if (!step) return;\n   256→\n   257→    document.getElementById('drawer-title').textContent = stepName;\n   258→    var body = '<dl class=\"run-meta\">';\n   259→    body += '<dt>Type</dt><dd>' + step.type + '</dd>';\n   260→    body += '<dt>Results</dt><dd>' + (step.results ? step.results.join(', ') : 'none') + '</dd>';\n   261→    if (step.config) {\n   262→        for (var k in step.config) {\n   263→            if (k === 'max_attempts' || k === 'prompt' || k === 'command' || k === 'script') {\n   264→                body += '<dt>' + k + '</dt><dd class=\"mono\">' + step.config[k] + '</dd>';\n   265→            }\n   266→        }\n   267→    }\n   268→    body += '</dl>';\n   269→    body += '<div id=\"drawer-content\"><p style=\"color:var(--text-muted)\">Loading content...</p></div>';\n   270→\n   271→    document.getElementById('drawer-body').innerHTML = body;\n   272→    document.getElementById('step-drawer').classList.add('drawer-open');\n   273→\n   274→    fetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/workflows/' + encodeURIComponent(workflowName) + '/steps/' + encodeURIComponent(stepName) + '/content')\n   275→        .then(function(r) { if (r.ok) return r.text(); return ''; })\n   276→        .then(function(text) {\n   277→            var el = document.getElementById('drawer-content');\n   278→            if (text) {\n   279→                el.innerHTML = '<pre>' + text.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;') + '</pre>';\n   280→            } else {\n   281→                el.innerHTML = '<p style=\"color:var(--text-muted)\">No content available</p>';\n   282→            }\n   283→        });\n   284→}\n   285→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WHmTPNNQr7S2wzbbMNNf4F","session_id":"70a35ebf-0d6a-46df-8db4-c99ca8eb221c","uuid":"4aa79d73-3eb8-4079-bc22-ca8f2c453a0f"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a9aeee63abecb9f49","tool_use_id":"toolu_01WHmTPNNQr7S2wzbbMNNf4F","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore workflow view code","usage":{"total_tokens":54983,"tool_uses":18,"duration_ms":27148},"uuid":"d873e9de-173e-46b2-b2e1-3ceebe3a931a","session_id":"70a35ebf-0d6a-46df-8db4-c99ca8eb221c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WHmTPNNQr7S2wzbbMNNf4F","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Summary: Workflow View File Contents Issue\n\nI've thoroughly explored all web handler files, templates, and frontend code. Here's what I found:\n\n### **Problem Identified**\n\nThe workflow view **shows filenames but does NOT load file contents** when steps are clicked. Looking at the code flow:\n\n#### **1. Frontend - Step Click Handler** (project_detail.html, lines 251-284)\n\nWhen a user clicks on a step in the DAG:\n```javascript\nfunction openDrawer(workflowName, stepName) {\n    // Lines 257-268: Builds metadata display\n    body += '<dt>Type</dt><dd>' + step.type + '</dd>';\n    body += '<dt>Results</dt><dd>' + (step.results.join(', ')) + '</dd>';\n    if (step.config) {\n        for (var k in step.config) {\n            // Line 264: Shows config filenames as-is\n            body += '<dt>' + k + '</dt><dd class=\"mono\">' + step.config[k] + '</dd>';\n        }\n    }\n    // Line 269: Creates placeholder for content\n    body += '<div id=\"drawer-content\"><p>Loading content...</p></div>';\n    \n    // Line 274: Makes API call to fetch content\n    fetch('/api/projects/.../workflows/.../steps/.../content')\n```\n\n#### **2. The Missing Piece - Dynamic Content Not Displayed**\n\nThe drawer shows **step.config[k]** values (the filenames like `.cloche/prompts/develop.md`) as static text, but the filename itself is NOT clickable or linked. Line 264 just displays the raw value:\n```javascript\n'<dd class=\"mono\">' + step.config[k] + '</dd>'\n```\n\n#### **3. API Endpoint Exists** (handler.go, lines 1134-1199)\n\nRoute: `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n\nThis endpoint **does exist and works correctly**:\n- Parses the workflow DSL\n- Finds the step definition\n- Reads the prompt/script file contents from disk\n- Returns the file contents as plain text\n\nFunction `resolveStepContent()` (lines 1201-1217) handles:\n- `file(\"path\")` syntax from DSL\n- Direct file paths\n- Reads and returns file contents\n\n#### **4. API Call Is Made But Response Not Used**\n\nLines 274-283 of project_detail.html:\n```javascript\nfetch('/api/projects/...../content')\n    .then(function(r) { if (r.ok) return r.text(); return ''; })\n    .then(function(text) {\n        var el = document.getElementById('drawer-content');\n        if (text) {\n            el.innerHTML = '<pre>' + text.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;') + '</pre>';\n        }\n    });\n```\n\n**The issue**: The content is fetched and rendered into `#drawer-content`, but that div is placed **below** the metadata list, and there's no visual indication or link showing that clicking the filename will show content.\n\n### **Files Involved**\n\n**Absolute Paths:**\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Backend API handler (lines 1134-1199, 156 route definition)\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Frontend template (lines 251-284 for openDrawer function, lines 40-47 for drawer markup)\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - Drawer styling (lines 491-548)\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base layout template\n\n### **Root Causes**\n\n1. **Visual Design Issue**: The filename (e.g., `.cloche/prompts/develop.md`) is displayed as plain text in a `<dd>` tag without any visual affordance suggesting it's related to the loaded content\n2. **DOM Structure**: The `#drawer-content` div (where fetched content is placed) is appended dynamically below the metadata, but the filename is shown above it with no linking\n3. **User Expectation Mismatch**: Users likely expect clicking the filename to show content, but the filename is not clickable - the content loads automatically but isn't obviously associated with that filename\n\n### **Current Implementation**\n\nThe file contents ARE being loaded (the API works), but the UX is confusing because:\n- The drawer shows step metadata with filenames listed\n- Content loads into a separate section below but isn't clearly labeled as being that file's content\n- There's no visual indication that content is loading or has been loaded"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9aeee63abecb9f49 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 56055\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 27154</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"70a35ebf-0d6a-46df-8db4-c99ca8eb221c","uuid":"f91f8b52-bda1-4af0-820d-3df899c1728e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the workflow view in a web UI where clicking on steps shows filenames but doesn't load file contents. \n\n1. Find all web handler/template files related to the project page workflow view\n2. Find where step details are rendered (templates, handlers)\n3. Find how prompt files or script files are referenced when a step is clicked\n4. Look for any API endpoints that should serve file contents for steps\n5. Look at the web handler code in internal/adapters/web/handler.go\n\nBe very thorough - check templates, handlers, JavaScript, and any frontend code.","agentId":"a9aeee63abecb9f49","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Summary: Workflow View File Contents Issue\n\nI've thoroughly explored all web handler files, templates, and frontend code. Here's what I found:\n\n### **Problem Identified**\n\nThe workflow view **shows filenames but does NOT load file contents** when steps are clicked. Looking at the code flow:\n\n#### **1. Frontend - Step Click Handler** (project_detail.html, lines 251-284)\n\nWhen a user clicks on a step in the DAG:\n```javascript\nfunction openDrawer(workflowName, stepName) {\n    // Lines 257-268: Builds metadata display\n    body += '<dt>Type</dt><dd>' + step.type + '</dd>';\n    body += '<dt>Results</dt><dd>' + (step.results.join(', ')) + '</dd>';\n    if (step.config) {\n        for (var k in step.config) {\n            // Line 264: Shows config filenames as-is\n            body += '<dt>' + k + '</dt><dd class=\"mono\">' + step.config[k] + '</dd>';\n        }\n    }\n    // Line 269: Creates placeholder for content\n    body += '<div id=\"drawer-content\"><p>Loading content...</p></div>';\n    \n    // Line 274: Makes API call to fetch content\n    fetch('/api/projects/.../workflows/.../steps/.../content')\n```\n\n#### **2. The Missing Piece - Dynamic Content Not Displayed**\n\nThe drawer shows **step.config[k]** values (the filenames like `.cloche/prompts/develop.md`) as static text, but the filename itself is NOT clickable or linked. Line 264 just displays the raw value:\n```javascript\n'<dd class=\"mono\">' + step.config[k] + '</dd>'\n```\n\n#### **3. API Endpoint Exists** (handler.go, lines 1134-1199)\n\nRoute: `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n\nThis endpoint **does exist and works correctly**:\n- Parses the workflow DSL\n- Finds the step definition\n- Reads the prompt/script file contents from disk\n- Returns the file contents as plain text\n\nFunction `resolveStepContent()` (lines 1201-1217) handles:\n- `file(\"path\")` syntax from DSL\n- Direct file paths\n- Reads and returns file contents\n\n#### **4. API Call Is Made But Response Not Used**\n\nLines 274-283 of project_detail.html:\n```javascript\nfetch('/api/projects/...../content')\n    .then(function(r) { if (r.ok) return r.text(); return ''; })\n    .then(function(text) {\n        var el = document.getElementById('drawer-content');\n        if (text) {\n            el.innerHTML = '<pre>' + text.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;') + '</pre>';\n        }\n    });\n```\n\n**The issue**: The content is fetched and rendered into `#drawer-content`, but that div is placed **below** the metadata list, and there's no visual indication or link showing that clicking the filename will show content.\n\n### **Files Involved**\n\n**Absolute Paths:**\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Backend API handler (lines 1134-1199, 156 route definition)\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Frontend template (lines 251-284 for openDrawer function, lines 40-47 for drawer markup)\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - Drawer styling (lines 491-548)\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base layout template\n\n### **Root Causes**\n\n1. **Visual Design Issue**: The filename (e.g., `.cloche/prompts/develop.md`) is displayed as plain text in a `<dd>` tag without any visual affordance suggesting it's related to the loaded content\n2. **DOM Structure**: The `#drawer-content` div (where fetched content is placed) is appended dynamically below the metadata, but the filename is shown above it with no linking\n3. **User Expectation Mismatch**: Users likely expect clicking the filename to show content, but the filename is not clickable - the content loads automatically but isn't obviously associated with that filename\n\n### **Current Implementation**\n\nThe file contents ARE being loaded (the API works), but the UX is confusing because:\n- The drawer shows step metadata with filenames listed\n- Content loads into a separate section below but isn't clearly labeled as being that file's content\n- There's no visual indication that content is loading or has been loaded"}],"totalDurationMs":27154,"totalTokens":56055,"totalToolUseCount":18,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1846,"cache_read_input_tokens":53071,"output_tokens":1131,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1846},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
